profile_positions.description:
in role of Technical Professional /Engineer my functions were:
Coordination of engineering team & Lab techs, technical development of
personnel;
Business development & technical advice‑customer interactions on regular basis,
customer basis included Wintershall, Vermilion, GdF, ONE BV, Tullow oil, TOTAL,
Lundin in NL and FR; Coordination of cementing operations onshore & offshore
(up to 10 active drilling rigs);
Cement design for onshore and offshore wells, based on geology & well architecture; 
Hydraulic simulations (Halliburton software Icem);
Elastomeric cement;
Light-weight cement applications;
Casing hardware advice; etc.
North Sea Sector offshore, offshore- the Netherlands, onshore- France;
familiar with Dutch mining authorities requirements and procedures;`
WellCat (Landmark) software;
Customer interaction on regular basis (technical support & business development);

My main functions were:
1) Service Quality: monitoring and tracking End of Job Customer surveys for all customers in Russia, leading investigations on cement job failures, implementing new technologies and methods to maximize efficiency of well isolation; interaction with Customer on quality issues ( preparation of Quality Review Presentations);

2) Service Quality & Health and Safety: performing field Service Quality Audits/HSE on the wellsite and at the bases, Behavior Based Performance, Hazard Cards, implementing corrective and improvement actions. Promoting and implementing HSE tools in Division;

3) Personnel Development; interacting with HRD to develop required skills of the workforce, identifying training needs for the project, providing some trainings myself;

4)Personnel Development; biggest achievement: Implementation of Competency Program for Cementing Services Personnel;

5)Finance: working closely with Managers and Order-To Cash, local engineers to forecast revenue and expense trends for division, participating in business planning;

6) Customer interaction and Business Development: Identifying Customer needs, planning jobs, interacting with customers to expand workscope.
